git config --global user.name "badhurudeen"
git config --global user.email "badhurudeen.s1@gmail.com"

git config user.name
git config user.email


To initilize the git:

	Cd-> target folder

	git init

To link remote repo:
	git remote add origin "https://github.com/badhurudeen/testing.git"


To get status:
   
   git status

To add a new file to the local repo:

	git add <filename.txt>

To commit:
	
	git commit -m "custom message"

To get the committed file status:

    git log

To push:

git push origin <master>

To Fetch:

git fetch origin <master>

To Pull:

git pull origin <firstbranch>

Files view:
 git ls-files

To create new branch:
	git branch <branch1>

To enter inside the branch:
	git checkout branch1

	add new file:
		git add <file.text>

	To commit
	    git commit -m "with message"	

To back to master:
	git checkout master	

To merge the branch with master;

    git merge <branch>		
